      <hr width="75%">
      <p align="center"><i>-ii-</i></p>
      
      <a name="about"></a><hr width="75%">
      <center><b>About the Author</b></center>
      
      <blockquote>Louis A. Pitschmann is the incoming dean of libraries at the University of Alabama. At the time of this report's publication,
         he was completing a fifteen-year tenure as associate director for collection development and management at the University
         of Wisconsin-Madison. Before that, he worked for almost a decade at the Cornell University Libraries. Mr. Pitschmann received
         his Ph.D. and M.L.S. from the University of Chicago. He has presented papers and written several articles on various aspects
         of collection development and management in research libraries.
      </blockquote>
      
      
      
      <hr width="75%">
      <p align="center"><i>-iii-</i></p>
      
      
      <hr width="75%">
